column168: TANK CAR DISCOVERED LEAKING ON 5 OF THE BOWL AT 4:30 AM.  TANK CAR HAD BEEN HUMPED AT 9:59 PM ON DECEMBER 30, COUPLING INTO RILX 112, LOADED COVERED H OPPER (END CAR OF AN ELEVEN CAR CUT).  AT 3:15 AM, LOADED BOX CAR NW 160155 WAS HUMPED INTO TRACK 5 AND COUPLED INTO THE TANK CAR. YARD AND ADJACENT M AINLINE SHUT DOWN ELECTRIC POWER, CABOOSES, ENGINES AND OTHER IGNITION SOUR CES WITHIN BOWL AREA.  RAILROAD AND SHIPPER RESPONSE TEAM EXAMINED THE CAR AND DETERMINED THAT A TRANSFER WAS FEASIBLE.  PRODUCT TRANSFERRD TO GATX 26 363 BEGINNING APPROXIMATELY 6PM AND FINISHED 11:09 AM, JANUARY 1. TANK CAR WAS PRESSURE PURGED WITH NITROGEN SIX(6) TIMES ON JANUARY 2 AND IS BEING RE TURNED TO ORIGIN PLANT FOR WATER WASHING BEFORE BEING SENT TO REPAIR FACILI TY AND INSPECTION TO DETERMINE ORIGIN OF LEAK. GATX 26363 BEING RETURNED TO TAFT FOR REPROCESSING TO ASSURE THAT PRODUCT IS WITHIN QUALITY CONTROL PAR AMETERS.  PRELIMINARY AND DETAILED MECHANICAL INSPECTION OF NW 160155, RAIX 7033, RILX 112 SHOW NO EVIDENCE OF OVERSPEED IMPACT. HUMP COMPUTER RECORDS INDICATE THAT RAIX 7033 AND NW 160155 EXITED THE LAST RETARDED WELL WITHIN DESIRED SPEEDS. APPROXIMATELY 1500 PEOPLE WERE EVACUATED FROM A ONE MILE R ADIUS AREA AS A PRECAUTION ONLY OF FIRE. AS THE MAJORITY OF THE MATERIAL EV APORATED ON RELEASE, ARKANSAS DEPARTMENT OF POLLUTION CONTROL AND ECOLOGY O KAYED THE LEAVING OF THE REMAINING SPILLED MATERIAL AS IT POSED NO ENVIRONM ENTAL HAZARD WITH DETECTABLE LEVELS IN THE DRAINAGE OUTFALLS BEING LESS THA N 1 PPB.  SEE ALSO REPORT NUMBER 85010100.
